<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-11-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-11-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="1108" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1108">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/16755.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Belt</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hermanas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-09">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 9, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Foreign Secretary in conference this morning, when I brought up
                            discussion of recent developments, border situation, stated this
                            question <pb facs="0936" n="820" xml:id="pg_820"/> would be entirely
                            settled when the Chief Executive reached Matamoros; that already
                            arrangements had been made whereby American forces could pursue bandits
                            for a distance of fifteen leagues into Mexican territory; and that
                            Mexican soldiers would have a like privilege when in pursuit of bandit
                            bands causing trouble. He further assured me orders had been issued for
                            the Mexican Secret Service to assist the military authorities to locate
                            and punish offenders operating in vicinity of the international
                            boundary.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Belt.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>